President Trump and Chairman Kim of North Korea held a historic meeting at the Inter-Korean House of Freedom in Panmunjom. President Trump became the first U.S. President to visit North Korea. Both leaders expressed their willingness to eliminate the past conflicts and open a new future. President Trump mentioned the progress made and the positive things happening. He also invited Chairman Kim to visit the White House. President Moon of South Korea praised the efforts of both leaders and expressed hope for progress in future dialogues. President Trump thanked everyone for being present and acknowledged the significant change from conflict to cooperation in the region. Chairman Kim expressed gratitude for the opportunity and assistance.